# Card

A surface that groups related content and actions into a contained block.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/card

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  card.root([attribute.class("w-[320px]")], [
    card.header([], [
      card.title([], [html.text("Quick Start")]),
      card.description([], [html.text("Get configured in seconds.")]),
    ]),
    card.content([], [
      html.p([], [
        html.text("Install the CLI, add your first element, and ship."),
      ]),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

## Installation

Install this element and its dependencies with the Drip CLI:

```sh
gleam run -m drip -- add card
```

## Usage

```gleam
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/card

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  card.root([], [
    card.header([], [
      card.title([], [html.text("Title")]),
      card.description([], [html.text("Supporting description.")]),
    ]),
    card.content([], [html.text("Body content.")]),
  ])
}
```

## Examples

Extend a card with an image, eyebrow, action, or footer, size it for dense or hero layouts, or compose a form.

### Image

Set an image as the card's first or last child to render it edge-to-edge, flush with the card's corners.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/card

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  card.root([attribute.class("w-[320px]")], [
    html.img([
      attribute.src("/img/ridgeline-moonlight.svg"),
      attribute.alt("Moonlight and stars over layered mountain ridges"),
      attribute.class("block dark:hidden aspect-video w-full object-cover"),
    ]),
    html.img([
      attribute.src("/img/ridgeline-sunrise.svg"),
      attribute.alt("Sunrise over layered mountain ridges"),
      attribute.class("hidden dark:block aspect-video w-full object-cover"),
    ]),
    card.header([], [
      card.eyebrow([], [html.text("Featured")]),
      card.title([], [html.text("Ridgeline Overlook")]),
      card.description([], [html.text("From first light to the last star.")]),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

### Eyebrow

Add an eyebrow above the title to categorize the card or signal context.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/card

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  card.root([attribute.class("w-[320px]")], [
    card.header([], [
      card.eyebrow([], [html.text("New")]),
      card.title([], [html.text("Workspace insights")]),
      card.description([], [
        html.text("Track activity across every project in one place."),
      ]),
    ]),
    card.content([], [
      html.p([], [
        html.text("Commits, reviews, and deploys in one live feed."),
      ]),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

### Action

Anchor a control to the top-right of the header with the action slot.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/button
import ui/card

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  card.root([attribute.class("w-[360px]")], [
    card.header([], [
      card.title([], [html.text("Notifications")]),
      card.description([], [html.text("Manage how and when we email you.")]),
      card.action([], [
        button.button([button.ghost(), button.sm()], [html.text("Edit")]),
      ]),
    ]),
    card.content([], [
      html.p([], [
        html.text("A weekly digest, plus instant alerts for mentions."),
      ]),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

### Footer

Add a footer flush against the bottom edge, with a muted tint and a dividing top border.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/button
import ui/card

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  card.root([attribute.class("w-[360px]")], [
    card.header([], [
      card.title([], [html.text("Invite teammates")]),
      card.description([], [
        html.text("Send a magic link to add a new member."),
      ]),
    ]),
    card.content([], [
      html.p([], [
        html.text("New members get access as soon as they accept."),
      ]),
    ]),
    card.footer([], [
      button.button([button.primary(), button.sm()], [html.text("Send invite")]),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

### Sizes

Size a card to fit dense lists, standard layouts, or hero blocks using the size attributes.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/card

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  element.fragment([
    card.root([card.sm(), attribute.class("w-[260px]")], [
      card.header([], [
        card.title([], [html.text("Small")]),
        card.description([], [html.text("Compact and efficient.")]),
      ]),
      card.content([], [
        html.p([], [html.text("Tighter spacing for dense layouts.")]),
      ]),
    ]),
    card.root([card.md(), attribute.class("w-[260px]")], [
      card.header([], [
        card.title([], [html.text("Medium (default)")]),
        card.description([], [html.text("A balanced baseline.")]),
      ]),
      card.content([], [
        html.p([], [html.text("Standard spacing for most content.")]),
      ]),
    ]),
    card.root([card.lg(), attribute.class("w-[320px]")], [
      card.header([], [
        card.title([], [html.text("Large")]),
        card.description([], [html.text("Spacious and prominent.")]),
      ]),
      card.content([], [
        html.p([], [html.text("Roomier padding for hero blocks.")]),
      ]),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

### Form

Compose the header, content, and footer with field and input elements to build a self-contained form.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/button
import ui/card
import ui/field
import ui/text_field

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  card.root([attribute.class("w-[360px]")], [
    card.header([], [
      card.title([], [html.text("Sign in")]),
      card.description([], [
        html.text("Enter your credentials to access your account."),
      ]),
    ]),
    card.content([], [
      field.group([], [
        field.root(
          [
            field.vertical(),
          ],
          [
            field.label([attribute.for("login-email")], [html.text("Email")]),
            text_field.input([
              attribute.id("login-email"),
              attribute.type_("email"),
              attribute.placeholder("ada@glow.dev"),
            ]),
          ],
        ),
        field.root(
          [
            field.vertical(),
          ],
          [
            field.label([attribute.for("login-password")], [
              html.text("Password"),
            ]),
            text_field.input([
              attribute.id("login-password"),
              attribute.type_("password"),
            ]),
          ],
        ),
      ]),
    ]),
    card.footer([], [
      button.submit([button.primary(), button.full_width()], [
        html.text("Sign in"),
      ]),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

## API Reference

### Elements

The root container and the composable child elements that fill its regions.

| Element | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `card.root(attrs, children)` | The surface container that wraps the card's slots. |
| `card.header(attrs, children)` | Top region. Hosts the eyebrow, title, description, and action. |
| `card.eyebrow(attrs, children)` | Small uppercase label rendered above the title. |
| `card.title(attrs, children)` | Primary heading inside the header. |
| `card.description(attrs, children)` | Secondary supporting text inside the header. |
| `card.action(attrs, children)` | Trailing control in the header, aligned opposite the title. |
| `card.content(attrs, children)` | Main body region. |
| `card.footer(attrs, children)` | Bottom region. A bordered, tinted bar for actions or summary text. |

### Size Attributes

Adjusts the card's padding and title scale.

| Attribute | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `card.sm()` | Small, with tighter padding and a smaller title. |
| `card.md()` | Medium, the default; matches a card with no size attribute. |
| `card.lg()` | Large, with roomier padding and a larger title. |

### Selectors

CSS selectors stamped on the card's markup, available for overriding or layering app-specific styles.

| Selector | Matches |
| --- | --- |
| `[data-slot="card"]` | The root container. |
| `[data-size="sm\|md\|lg"]` | The root, tagged with its active size. |
| `[data-slot="card-header"]` | Top region of the card. |
| `[data-slot="card-eyebrow"]` | Uppercase label above the title. |
| `[data-slot="card-title"]` | Primary heading inside the header. |
| `[data-slot="card-description"]` | Supporting text inside the header. |
| `[data-slot="card-action"]` | Trailing control in the header. |
| `[data-slot="card-content"]` | Main body region. |
| `[data-slot="card-footer"]` | Bottom bar for actions or summary text. |

## Accessibility

**No implicit semantics.** A card renders as a plain container with no implicit landmark or heading semantics; it groups content visually, not structurally. When its title heads a navigable section, give it real heading semantics (for example, a heading element in the title slot) so it joins the document outline.

